div.p:
They have a Recreation certainly
deriv'd from their Anceſtours,
viz: La Mora, anciently
micare Digitis, at the firſt
it appeares but childiſhly ridiculous;
after better acquaintance,
a kinde of Conjuration;
Tis of force to binde the Fancy;
yet the moſt illiterate are
beſt at the Game.

               Palladius made this his Maſter-piece;
for tis ſo contriv'd,
that it containes Geometrically
a Round, a Croſſe, and a
Square.
